Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @Pecans{1/2%ounce}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Granny Smith Apple{1}. Peel @Orange{2} and divide into segments.

== Candied Bacon ==

Place @Bacon{4%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer and evenly sprinkle with half the @Chili Powder{1%teaspoon} and one packet of @Brown Sugar{3%tablespoon} (all the chili powder and two packets of brown sugar for 4 servings).

Bake on top rack until bacon is crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning! Your bacon might be done sooner.

== Pecan Streusel Topping ==

Place @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until softened, ~{20-30%seconds}. Stir in @Cinnamon{1%teaspoon}, pecans, and one packet of brown sugar (two packets for 4 servings) until thoroughly combined. Freeze until ready to use.

== Plum Jam Dipping Sauce ==

In a separate #small bowl{}, whisk @Plum Jam{1}, @Powdered Sugar{2%ounce}, and one packet of @Sour Cream{4.5%tablespoon} until combined and smooth. Wash and dry #whisk{}.

== Cup of Coffee Cake ==

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together remaining @Sour Cream{} and ¼ cup water until mostly smooth.

Add @Tempura Batter{82%g}, @Baking Powder{1/2%tablespoon}, @Maple Syrup{2%tablespoon}, remaining brown sugar, @Sugar{2%tablespoon}, and @Salt{1/2%tsp}; whisk until thoroughly combined.

Coat two #microwave-safe mugs{} with @Nonstick Cooking Spray{}. Evenly pour batter into #mugs{}.

Microwave until batter is almost set, ~{1-2%minutes}. Evenly crumble streusel topping over mug muffins. Microwave in 30-second intervals until a #toothpick{} inserted into the center comes out clean and muffins spring back to the touch.

== To Serve ==

Divide mug muffins, candied bacon, apple slices, and orange segments between plates. Serve jam dipper on the side for dipping.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.